tweet: Grizzly bears in Yellowstone region should be delisted. Unfortunately, a judge relisted them in the face of wildlife management experts & scientific evidence. This new bill would delist them again & stop further frivolous litigation. https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/news-releases?ID=EBE8AB51-3729-49A8-B142-DC344E2F190F …

I intro’d legislation w/ @RepLizCheney that would direct the Department of the Interior to reissue its delisting of the grizzly bear in the Greater Yellowstone Ecosystem and prohibit further judicial review on this issue.  https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/news-releases?ID=EBE8AB51-3729-49A8-B142-DC344E2F190F …
It’s clear that under the Endangered Species Act grizzly bears in the Yellowstone region are fully recovered, that they should be delisted and management returned to the states.

This common-sense legislation would ensure that if you’re traveling from point A to point C with a knife that is legal in both locations, you should not have to worry about going through point B. https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2019/2/enzi-wyden-introduce-bill-to-protect-law-abiding-knife-owners …

Intro’d a bill w/ @RonWyden today to ensure that those traveling with a properly secured knife are not prosecuted under local or state laws which ban certain knives.  https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/news-releases?ID=67702854-8D32-4956-9810-B21FE99AA2B8 …

I am proud to cosponsor a bipartisan Senate resolution designating Feb 16-23, 2019 as National FFA Week. https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2019/2/enzi-applauds-senate-passage-of-national-ffa-week-resolution …

When an animal is categorized as an endangered species,  states & communities are most impacted but they can’t verify, dispute or complement the info. WY has some of the richest wildlife habitat in the world - we should encourage an open process that uses the best data available.

Introduced legislation w/ @SenatorRisch and @SenPatRoberts that would require the federal government to disclose the data it uses for Endangered Species Act listings. https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2019/2/states-deserve-a-seat-at-the-table-when-listing-species-as-endangered …

If you travel w/ a bow for hunting, you shouldn't have to worry that a shortcut through a nat'l park could find you in legal jeopardy. The Senate passed a bill that included language to allow bows & archery equipment to be transported across federal land. https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2019/2/senate-acts-to-protect-bow-owners-traveling-through-national-parks …

Closing an IRS office at any time creates problems for taxpayers in Wyoming. But it is particularly burdensome when it occurs during the filing season – and the first one after our comprehensive tax reform – when folks continue to learn how to comply with new tax changes.

I’m troubled by the recent closure of the IRS taxpayer assistance center in Cheyenne. I sent a letter requesting it be reopened as quickly as possible. https://www.enzi.senate.gov/public/index.cfm/2019/2/enzi-asks-irs-to-reopen-taxpayer-assistance-center-in-cheyenne …
